5000|$|The {{history of}} anti-communist <b>red-baiting</b> in general, and McCarthyism in particular, {{continues}} to be hotly debated, and political divisions this controversy created continue to make themselves felt. Conservative critics contend that revelations such as the Venona project decryptions and the FBI Silvermaster File at least mute if not outright refute the charge that <b>red-baiting</b> in general was unjustified. Historian Nicholas von Hoffman wrote in The Washington Post that evidence revealed in the Venona project forced him to admit that McCarthy was [...] "closer to the truth than those who ridiculed him".|$|R
