50|$|In 1950, Anita and Henry Willcox, {{with three}} of their five children, founded a {{community}} in Norwalk, Connecticut called Village Creek. Conceived as a haven from racism, the Cold War, and McCarthy era <b>red-baiting,</b> Village Creek became the first inter-racial cooperative on the Eastern seaboard of the United States. Village Creek today comprises some sixty houses; in 2010 it was declared a National Historical Monument.|$|R
